French Finance Minister Edouard Balladurdiscussed the need to control public spending in talks heretoday with British Chancellor of the Exchequer Nigel Lawson, aTreasury spokesman said.    The spokesman said the ministers reviewed their economies,and public spending, domestic and European Community-wide.    He declined to comment on whether the subject of concertedaction to shore up the dollar had arisen. The U.S. Currencydipped sharply earlier this week after a month of relativestability after an agreement by six major industrialisednations in Paris on February 22 to stabilise their currencies.REUTER&#3;